{
  "_id": "ffiFA6XOcHaeFEBW",
  "name": "Mental Discord",
  "type": "feat",
  "img": "systems/pf1/icons/feats/leadership.jpg",
  "data": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>As a standard action, you can expend 1 point of mental focus to disrupt the mind of one living creature within 30 feet. The creature can attempt a Will saving throw to negate the effect. If it fails the save, the creature can’t concentrate on any spell effects and must succeed at a concentration check to cast any spell (DC = 15 + double the spell level). The affected creature takes a –4 penalty on this check if the spell includes a thought component. The creature takes a –2 penalty on all Will saving throws while under this effect.</p>\n<p>This effect lasts for 1 round per occultist level you possess.</p>"
    },
